            . I am a special constable. At a quarter before six o'clock on the morning of the 18th of August, I saw the prisoner and another walking to and fro, in <placeName id="t18270913-199-crimeloc1129">Torrington-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-199-crimeloc1129" type="placeName" value="Torrington-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-199-crimeloc1129" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-199-off1127 t18270913-199-crimeloc1129"></join> - I watched them, and saw the prisoner take a cord from his pocket, and drop it down the area of No. 4; he drew up this kettle, put it under his arm, and gave the cord to the other - I went up and took him with the kettle; he said he had done it for a lark.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-199-person1817">
                  MARY 
                  STALLAN
               <interp inst="t18270913-199-person1817" type="surname" value="STALLAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-199-person1817" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-199-person1817" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mrs. Rebecca Southey(who is single), at No. 4, Torrington-square; this is her kettle - I had set it out about a quarter of an hour before; the constable came and asked if it was mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It was not done with an intention to rob.</p>
